                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 2: Inflation rose marginally to 0.31 per cent for the week ended March 21 from 0.27 per cent the week before, after declining for eight consecutive weeks. Analysts believe that inflation could turn negative in the coming weeks, which will give headroom to the RBI to cut rates in its monetary policy slated for April 21. Inflation was 7.8 per cent in the corresponding period last year                            
	 New Delhi, April 2: The mutual fund industry has witnessed a decline of over Rs 7,000 crore in its assets in March, plunging below the Rs 5-lakh-crore mark. HDFC Mutual Fund added over Rs 1,000 crore to its assets under management during the month.                            
	 Mumbai, April 2: Reliance Capital Trustee, a Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group firm, has increased its stake in Bombay Dyeing amp; Manufacturing Company to 5.19 per cent from 4.23 per cent. Reliance Capital Trustee bought over 3.70 lakh equity shares on March 30 for over Rs 5.99 crore.                             
	 New Delhi, April 2: India will launch the auction of oil and gas blocks under Nelp on April 9, offering 70 areas for bidding.                                                                                                                            
